references: The detailed statistics of the databases used in this research are outlined in Table 3. The ASVspoof database is a series of data from the ASVspoof challenges [8, 9, 10, 11]. Among them, 19LA is one of the most widely used datasets by industry researchers. For this research, we use the ASVspoof 2019 LA (19LA) [10] datasets as our primary experimental dataset. Noisy and reverberant datasets are generated based on this dataset. The 19LA dataset consists mostly of clean data created using utterances from 107 speakers (46 male, 61 female) from the VCTK dataset . These 107 speakers are partitioned into three speaker-disjoint sets for training, development, and evaluation. The spoofed utterances were generated using four TTS and two VC algorithms in the training and development sets, while 13 TTS/VC algorithms are used in the evaluation set, 4 of which are partially known and 7 of which are unknown for training and development.
